<paragraph blockId="11.[136,886,1316,1343]" box="[136,886,1316,1343]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<heading box="[136,886,1316,1343]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S.M. Boo" authorityName="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S. M. Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,699,1316,1343]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="ulixei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,336,1316,1343]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Sargassum ulixei</emphasis>
G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S.M. Boo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[711,796,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[711,796,1317,1342]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[810,878,1316,1342]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1511,1533]" captionTargetBox="[363,1229,201,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[357,1229,190,1487]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphology of Sargassum ulixei sp. nov. A. Habit. B, C. Section of axial cells (a) and medullar cells (m). D. Holdfast. E. Sessile blades (arrow head), vesicles (arrow), and receptacles growing above the branch. F–H. Receptacles, zygote (z)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5150062" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5150062/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1385,1623]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
Thalli with a disc, crustose or conical holdfast. Stipe cylindrical and smooth, blades lanceolate to elliptic, sessile, 
<quantity box="[1238,1318,1385,1407]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
in length and 1.0– 
<quantity box="[231,305,1421,1443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
wide. Nerve expanded, ecostate or faint, with smooth margins. Cryptostomata present. Vesicles elliptical, with smooth margins, sessile, 
<quantity box="[358,440,1457,1479]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
in length. The apical part of the vesicle has a short apicula. Receptacles cylindrical to elliptical, with smooth margins&gt; 
<quantity box="[362,415,1493,1515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in length, growing in bunches with blades. Thalli up to 
<quantity box="[946,1004,1493,1514]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
in length, with terete axes and smooth primary axes arising from the stipe, giving rise to numerous secondary branches. Secondary branches 
<quantity box="[1087,1134,1529,1551]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
in length in some thalli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
