<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1662,2076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,302,1662,1688]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The species epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S. M. Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[538,600,1662,1688]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="ulixei">
<emphasis box="[538,600,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">ulixei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ refers to the character in Homer’s Odyssey, giving credit to the long trips and difficulties encountered when studying the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andrade-Sorcia &amp; Riosmena-Rodríguez &amp; Muñiz-Salazar &amp; López-Vivas &amp; Boo &amp; Lee &amp; Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[667,789,1698,1724]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[667,789,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Sargassum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxonomy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1662,2076]" box="[189,911,1732,1759]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1732,1758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Habitat:—</emphasis>
Growth was observed on rocks in the intertidal zone.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1662,2076]" box="[189,877,1767,1794]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,473,1767,1793]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Current distribution:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation box="[473,873,1767,1794]" location="Kino Bay" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sonora">
